abstract: NFL Roundup; New York Jets owner Woody Johnson dismisses worries about investigation into whether team broke league rules on tampering before it signed free-agent cornerback Darrelle Revis; other football news noted.
lead_paragraph: Johnson said he was not worried about an N.F.L. investigation into whether the Jets broke tampering rules before signing cornerback Darrelle Revis.

headline.main: Jets Owner Woody Johnson Says He’s Not Concerned About Tampering Inquiry
